    "The theory of communication under secrecy systems first appeared at Bells Systems, which defines converting a set of plaintext information into a set of possible ciphers.",
    "A common encryption strategy is known as the symmetric encryption scheme.",
    "The block cipher operates in various modes to provide confidentiality approved by NIST.",
    "The process of the aforementioned system entails the sharing of a secret key between the many people engaged in private communication.",
    "The primary objective of an asymmetric encryption scheme is to allow the encryption algorithm to be public while keeping the key secret."
